  "text": "A good example of decreasing energy efficiency under regulated markets is the switch from mainly supercritical to subcritical coal power during the 1970s and 1980s. Yeh and Rubin and maintenance costs [CITATION_1] . Lowered demand for new electricity investments usually favored smaller, subcritical investments. Recent developments have, however, seen a moderate increase in supercritical plant construction in the U.S. In general however, the majority of the U.S. coal fleet was built in the 1970s and 1980s, and thus is decreasing in efficiency due to age [CITATION_2] .",
